:: Alexandra2 {"position":"1000,500","size":"100,100"}
Alexandra Bodovora: Oh it's dreadful, just absolutely awful... those people are beastly! 

> (link-goto: "What is the matter ?", "Alexandra3")


:: Alexandra3 {"position":"1000,600","size":"100,100"}
Alexandra Bodovora: It's Stefan, the poor dear just got his first job last month, and they just fired him for nothing at all! All he did was raise his voice a little at his boss... but you know how young men are, right? I tried to go talk to the manager, but they told me he has anger issues. Can you believe such a ridiculous thing? My son is an angel, and he deserves better than a crummy old job. I'm going to try to get him to get a degree... that way he can be the one to boss those no good idiots around!

> (link-goto:"Ha, that's a smart plan! I always say the world has gotten too hard on young boys, at least your son has character.", "ReassureAlexandra")
<br>
> (link-goto:"Well, Alexandra... I know you mean well, but I've known you and your son for a while, and he can be a bit hot-headed. Maybe you should let him learn from his mistakes... this time at least?  ", "ConfrontAlexandra")


:: AlexandraD3A {"position":"4800,500","size":"100,100"}
Alexandra Bodovora: Then you must give him all my thanks, for giving my son's life purpose when he most needed it.

(link-goto: "She pays and leaves.", "EndDay3")


:: AlexandraD3B {"position":"4900,500","size":"100,100"}
Alexandra Bodovora: My son will come back a hero, or not at all. Don't worry, I know he is brave, and I pray everyday to keep him safe.

(link-goto: "She pays and leaves.", "EndDay3")


:: AlexandraD3C {"position":"5000,500","size":"100,100"}
Alexandra Bodovora: I am... But secretly I am so worried that those beasts might hurt my dear baby. I will be happiest when this is all over and he is returned to me.

(link-goto: "She pays and leaves.", "EndDay3")


:: AlexandraD3Start {"position":"4850,250","size":"100,100"}
17:00 - Alexandra Bodovora arrives.

> (link-goto: "Good Afternoon Miss Bodovora, you seem in high spirits today.", "AlexandraD3_1")


:: AlexandraD3_1 {"position":"4850,375","size":"100,100"}
Alexandra Bodovora: I'm here to celebrate; my son has joined the resistance and I've never been so proud of him! Give me everything sweet and any spirits you have left... Tomorrow he will go to war.

(if: $HasFlyer is true)[(She notices the flyer)

Alexandra Bodovora: And I see you too understand the importance of this, congratulations on doing your bit in helping to save our country. These flyers are a wonderful idea.

> (link-goto: "Actually they were made by a good friend of mine, a smart young man named Alexander Ben Hassim that has been searching for his place in this war.","AlexandraD3A" )
](else:)[What do you think, aren't you proud of my boy?

> (link-goto:"Of course I am... But aren't you worried for his safety? What if something, god forbid, were to happen to him?", "AlexandraD3B")
<br>
> (link-goto:"Your son is the hero we all aspire to be, you must be the proudest of mothers !", "AlexandraD3C")
]


:: AlexandraD51 {"position":"6375,425","size":"100,100"}
Alexandra Bodovora: They were preparing for an ambush, then the fighting began... they say it was over before it even began, that they shot right through his lung. He would have fought for his country and died alone, suffocating in the mud! Those monsters shot him before he even got a chance to fight... to live...

> (link-goto: "Death is always ugly, but your son was a true hero, and his name will not be forgotten. You have given us the greatest gift and most bitter sacrifice, I cannot begin to thank you enough, or comprehend your sorrow.", "AD5A")
<br>
> (link-goto:"It is a tragedy... A horrible, meaningless loss. All my condolences.", "AD5B")


:: AlexandraD5ProposeLeave {"position":"6450,675","size":"100,100"}
Alexandra Bodovora: My memories live here... They took my son, but I won’t let them take my home. Good luck, and may we meet again.

(link-goto: "She leaves.", "LunaD5Start")


:: AlexandraD5Start {"position":"6375,300","size":"100,100"}
10:00 - You see Alexandra Bodovora arrive. She looks devastated.


Alexandra Bodovora: He is dead. My son is dead.

> (link-goto: "Oh dear, what happened?", "AlexandraD51")


:: AlexandraD5Understand {"position":"6325,675","size":"100,100"}
Alexandra Bodovora: Thank you. Good luck to you, and may we meet again.

(link-goto: "She leaves.", "LunaD5Start")


:: AlexandraStart {"position":"1000,300","size":"100,100"}
10:00 - A customer arrives.

> (link-goto:"Good morning madam Bodovora, how are things going today?", "Alexandra2")


:: BenHassim1 {"position":"3100,400","size":"100,100"}
Alexander Ben Hassim: I was just coming for some food... but on the way here I saw... she was lying face down... A child... Killed by a missile. They are monsters.

> (link-goto: "I'm scared too Alex, I just wish there was something I could do to protect my friends.", "BenHassim2")


:: BenHassim2 {"position":"3100,500","size":"100,100"}
Alexander Ben Hassim: So do I... I feel helpless in the midst of all of this.

> (link-goto: "It's not your job to worry about everyone, the government will take care of us. In the meantime, try not to worry too much", "BenHassim3")
<br>
> (link-goto: "None of us is completely helpless. I am sure you can find your own way to contribute.", "BenHassim3")


:: BenHassim2Accept {"position":"4175,550","size":"100,100"}
Alexander Ben Hassim: You are a true brother, and a hero of the people.

(link:"He leaves.")[
(set: $HasFlyer to true)
(go-to:"LunaD3Start")
]


:: BenHassim2Refuse {"position":"4275,550","size":"100,100"}
Alexander Ben Hassim: I understand... No hard feelings, I know your sympathies lie with us, but it was unfair of me to ask so much of you.

(link:"He leaves.")[
(set: $HasFlyer to false)
(go-to:"LunaD3Start")
]


:: BenHassim2Start {"position":"4225,250","size":"100,100"}
14:00 - Alexander Ben Hassim arrives.

> (link-goto: "Oh, hello Alexander.", "BenHassim2_1")


:: BenHassim2_1 {"position":"4225,350","size":"100,100"}
Alexander Ben Hassim: I thought a lot about what you told me... and I figured out what to do!

> (link-goto:"That's wonderful, it's important to keep busy right now... with everything going on.", "BenHassim2_2")


:: BenHassim2_2 {"position":"4225,450","size":"100,100"}
Alexander Ben Hassim: That's exactly why I organized this group of resistance fighters, to protect civilians like yourself and fight for our freedom. I even had some flyers made, and I want to put them up everywhere so all the young men can do their bit too. Sooo, do you mind if I put up some of my flyers in your window? You would be doing the cause a great service if you accepted my offer.

> (link-goto:"I'm sorry my friend, but I'm an old man, all alone in this shop... and those little flyers of yours are going to paint a target right onto the front of my shop.", "BenHassim2Refuse")
<br>
> (link-goto:"It's not without risk, but I must help out however possible. Yes, you can put them up, but be careful, this is not a game.", "BenHassim2Accept")



:: BenHassim3 {"position":"3100,600","size":"100,100"}
(link-goto: "He smiles, pays and leaves.", "MikhailStart")


:: BenHassimStart {"position":"3100,275","size":"100,100"}
12:00 - You see a young man, who you recognize to be Alexander Ben Hassim, a student who lives a few blocks away.

> (link-goto: "Hello Alexander, what can I do for you today?", "BenHassim1")


:: BetrayedBeatUp {"position":"5550,2025","size":"100,100"}
Vlad: War is hell. At least you're alive. Besides, I never did like that Ben Hassim character, he’s a real know it all.

> (link-goto: "He doesn’t deserve to die... How can you be so cold ?", "Drink1")


:: BetrayedSafe {"position":"5675,2050","size":"100,100"}
Vlad: War is hell. At least you are okay. Besides, I never did like that Ben Hassim character, he’s a real know it all.

> (link-goto: "He doesn’t deserve to die... How can you be so cold ?", "Drink1")


:: ConfrontAlexandra {"position":"1075,750","size":"100,100"}
Ms. Bodovora: Huh, I see. Well at least my son is around, when did you last speak to your daughter eh?

> (link-goto: "It's been... weeks.", "ConfrontAlexandra1")


:: ConfrontAlexandra1 {"position":"1075,875","size":"100,100"}
Ms. Bodovora: Look, I didn't mean it like that... But you know, I'm a mama bear, ever since... you know, since I've been alone, I've wanted to protect him and make him strong.


> (link:"I understand, we are both doing what we think is best...")[I understand, we are both doing what we think is best...<br>
(link-goto:"She pays for her groceries and leaves.", "LunaStart")]


:: D4Interruption {"position":"5475,1275","size":"100,100"}
As you begin to emerge from the basement, you hear a crashing noise. You cautiously approach the shop's entrance.

Five Russian soldiers stand in your shop, picking what they might from your stalls.

> (link-goto:"Hey, you broke my door!", "SoldiersConfront")
<br>
> (link-goto:"Welcome to my humble corner shop, what might I get you?", "SoldiersConfront")


:: Danya1 {"position":"3700,350","size":"100,100"}
Danya Kovalenko: Well... please don't tell anyone, but I need an emergency bag.

> (link-goto: "I'm sorry to meddle but... are you sure? I met your husband the other day and he told me you all planned to stay and protect the farm, he will be heartbroken to leave it", "Danya2")


:: Danya2 {"position":"3700,450","size":"100,100"}
Danya Kovalenko: That's why it's a secret... I don't think Mik will want to join us, and I won't let him stop us. I heard gunfire last night, and I won't allow for my babies to get hurt.

(link:"...")[Stella Kovalenko: Daddy says it's our job to protect the farm. I'm going to be strong like him. I'm a Ukrainian!

(link:"...")[Danya Kovalenko: Please...

> (link-goto:"I'll do what I can to help, here.", "DanyaAccept")
<br>
> (link-goto:"Why don't you talk about it with Mikhail ?", "DanyaRefuse")

]
]


:: DanyaAccept {"position":"3800,575","size":"100,100"}
Danya Kovalenko: Thank you for understanding.


(link-goto: "She pays and leaves with her daughter.", "NinaD3Start")


:: DanyaRefuse {"position":"3650,575","size":"100,100"}
Danya Kovalenko: I have, but he's not listening to me. Still, thank you for the bag.

(link-goto: "She pays and leaves with her daughter", "NinaD3Start")


:: Day3Start {"position":"3700,250","size":"100,100"}
**27 february 2024**

After the initial shock of the air raids and Russian army incursion on Ukraine's territory, the fighting is getting closer to Irpin. You can hear the firefights in Bucha, just a few kilometers away.

Even then, you see Danya Kovalenko and her daugter coming to the shop.

> (link-goto:"Good morning Danya and Stella, what can I do for you today?", "Danya1")


:: Day4Start {"position":"5500,275","size":"100,100"}
**28 february 2022**

Since yesterday, the Russians have advanced into Irpin. You've been sleeping in the basement for weeks, it helps you feel safe. You can hear the fighting going on all around. You haven't seen any soldiers yet, but you know they are close.

(set: $betrayedBenHassim to false)
> (link: "Open the shop as usual.")[
(go-to: "Day4StartOpen")
]
<br>
> (link: "Stay put.")[
(go-to: "Day4StartClosed")
]


:: Day4StartClosed {"position":"5450,400","size":"100,100"}
You stay in the basement, decided to wait it out. You have enough to eat and drink for a little while.

However, you quickly hear banging on the front door.

(link-goto: "Go upstairs.", "Day4StartClosed_2")


:: Day4StartClosed_2 {"position":"5450,500","size":"100,100"}
As you approach the door, you see it's your friend Vlad.

Vlad: Open ! Quick ! The Russians are here !

> (link-goto: "Your Russian friends are causing quite a ruckus outside, huh?", "VladD41")


:: Day4StartOpen {"position":"5550,400","size":"100,100"}
As you open the door, you see Vlad, out of breath, rushing towards you. He pushes you inside and closes the door.

Vlad: What is wrong with you? The Russians are here! You can’t be open today!

> (link-goto:"I guess you are right... Your Russian friends are causing quite a ruckus outside, huh?", "VladD41")
<br>
> (link-goto:"My door has always been open, no matter what is going on out there. I’m not going to start disappointing my regulars when they need me most.", "VladD41")


:: Day5Start {"position":"6050,275","size":"100,100"}
**3rd march 2022**

After the violent combats all around the shop, the ukrainian army managed to push the Russian forces out of Irpin and Bucha. They discover the massacre that unfolded there.

Your neighborhood is almost unrecognizable. The house across the street was destroyed with an artillery shell. It could have been you.

You're busy repairing the door of your shop, when you see Mikhail Kovalenko arrive.

> (link-goto:"Good day, how are you doing?", "MikhailD51")


:: Drink1 {"position":"5675,2175","size":"100,100"}
Vlad: As I said, war is hell. You didn’t deserve to be looted(if:$beatUp > 0)[ and beat up], but I know how to deal with all this ugliness. Look, I hid some vodka down here, behind your fridge... y’know, for emergencies.

> (link-goto:"What is wrong with you? The world is ending around us, we are surrounded by enemies, and you want to open another bottle!?", "Drink2")


:: Drink2 {"position":"5525,2300","size":"100,100"}
Vlad: Listen to me. When your life imploding on itself, there is no better cure than a deck of cards, a large bottle and a friendly face! Come, let’s keep living how we’ve always lived, until we can’t anymore.

> (link-goto:"Do you really want to live like this?", "Drink3")


:: Drink3 {"position":"5525,2400","size":"100,100"}
Vlad: This is where you belong. besides, who will I play against if you leave?

> (link-goto:"But my shop is destroyed... there is nothing left for me here. I’m thinking of leaving...", "Drink4")


:: Drink4 {"position":"5525,2500","size":"100,100"}
Vlad: *Na zdoróvʹje* my friend, to whatever path you choose.

> (link-goto: "Na zdoróvʹje, my friend...", "EndDay4")


:: End {"position":"7125,300","size":"100,100"}
> (link-goto: "Leave Ukraine.", "LeaveUkraine")
<br>
> (link-goto: "Stay", "EndStay")


:: EndDay1 {"position":"2250,300","size":"100,100"}
That's it. No one else is coming today. While closing the shop, you think about the danger, if a war is really brewing. If it happens, what will you do ? It's always good to be prepared.

[[Prepare an emergency suitcase]]


:: EndDay3 {"position":"5250,275","size":"100,100"}
As the day comes to a close, you can hear the combat continue in the distance. You call your daughter, in Berlin. She is safe. She begs you to come join her.

You think about your shop. (if: $extra_refill is false)[Your stocks are dwindling.](else:)[You still have some stock, but it won't last forever.] The people here need you.


> (link-goto: "Leave Ukraine.", "LeaveUkraine")
<br>
> (link-goto: "Stay", "Day4Start")


:: EndDay4 {"position":"5850,275","size":"100,100"}
> (link-goto: "Leave Ukraine.", "LeaveUkraine")
<br>
> (link-goto: "Stay", "Day5Start")


:: EndInterruptionBeatUp {"position":"5525,1775","size":"100,100"}
The soldiers finally leave. Your whole body hurts, and they still took whatever they wanted. As you're contemplating the situation, you hear Vlad's voice from the stairwell.

Vlad: What happened up there?
(set: $passedOut to false)
> (link-goto: "Some soldiers showed up and stole everything I had left... They beat me up, and I’m completely ruined now.", "Looters1")

> (link-goto: "I betrayed my friend... And they still stole everything.", "BetrayedBeatUp")



:: EndInterruptionPassOut {"position":"5400,1775","size":"100,100"}
You wake up in pain. The cold neon light of your basement blinds you.

Vlad: You’re finally awake! What did those awful rioters do to you? I head a loud noise and came up straight away!  I found you on the ground, unconscious. I was afraid... you wouldn’t wake up.
(set: $passedOut to true)
> (link-goto: "Rioters, Vlad? Is that what you think? I was lucky enough to receive a visit from our lovely Russian allies. Your friends up there took everything I had left...", "Looters1")


:: EndInterruptionSafe {"position":"5675,1775","size":"100,100"}
The soldiers finally leave. Your store is in bad shape, but at least you're safe. As you're contemplating the situation, you hear Vlad's voice from the stairwell.

Vlad: What happened up there?
(set: $passedOut to false)
> (link-goto: "Some soldiers showed up and stole everything I had left...they didn’t hurt me, but I’m completely ruined now.", "Safe1")


:: EndStay {"position":"7275,300","size":"100,100"}
You join Vlad at his place.

Vlad: "Ah, my friend, come to say goodbye ?"

> (link-goto: "I'm staying. Let's raise a glass to the new normal. There is plenty to do here.", "EndStay2")


:: EndStay2 {"position":"7400,300","size":"100,100"}
The war is far from over. The threat of missiles and bombs still looms over your head, but you managed to keep your spirits high. You don't know what the future holds, but you will help rebuild it.

(link-goto: "The end.", "Start")


:: GiftLollipop {"position":"1200,550","size":"100,100"}
Gabi Luna: Thank you thank you! You know, ever since we moved here, you’ve been so nice to me and my boy, and now you made our day!

(link-goto:"She pays for the rest of her groceries and leaves with her son.", "NinaStart")


:: InterrogationLie {"position":"5450,1625","size":"100,100"}
Soldier: Are you sure? It would be a shame if you were lying to us.

(link-goto: "He hits you.", "AfterHit")



:: KovalenkoFamily {"position":"1725,425","size":"100,100"}
Danya Kovalenko: Great!

(link:"...")[Mikhail Kovalenko: Well... everyone has their own little issues don't they?

(link-goto:"Of course... is Stella having trouble at school? She is so sweet, I hope no one is picking on her.", "KovalenkoFamily2")]


:: KovalenkoFamily2 {"position":"1725,525","size":"100,100"}
Danya Kovalenko: Actually it's Peter...


(link-goto:"Oh I see, but I thought he was done with school, working on the farm with you Mikhail.", "KovalenkoFamily3")


:: KovalenkoFamily3 {"position":"1725,625","size":"100,100"}
Mikhail Kovalenko: He is... but he doesn't seem to like it, he keeps talking about some fancy art school in Strasbourg... He even said he wanted a better life than me and my father and his father... Whatever that means.

(link:"...")[Danya Kovalenko: Well he is young, still figuring things out. Of course we'd love for him to stay, but...

(link:"...")[Mikhail Kovalenko: But nothing, he's just having a little teenage tantrum, that's all.

> (link:"It would sure be a shame for the farm's legacy to be lost, I hope it works out for all of you.")[It would sure be a shame for the farm's legacy to be lost, I hope it works out for all of you.<br>
(link-goto:"They pay for their groceries and leave.", "LennyStart")]]]


:: KovalenkoFarm {"position":"1850,425","size":"100,100"}
Mikhail Kovalenko: Not yet, but as soon as the ground thaws properly we will be back at it, as always.

(link-goto:"I sure hope so. My pops used to send me to get his eggs from your father, the Kovalenko farm is a landmark of our town.", "KovalenkoFarm2")


:: KovalenkoFarm2 {"position":"1850,525","size":"100,100"}
Mikhail Kovalenko: I remember... you were young then, about as old as Peter is now as a matter of fact!

(link-goto: "And you were only a small boy, but already so eager to follow in your father's footsteps.", "KovalenkoFarm3")


:: KovalenkoFarm3 {"position":"1850,625","size":"100,100"}
Mikhail Kovalenko: As any boy would. Now, let's get some supplies and head back to work, Danya has promised us all warm apple cake when Peter and I finish up repairing the barn roof.

(link-goto:"They pay for their groceries and leave.", "LennyStart")


:: KovalenkoStart {"position":"1800,300","size":"100,100"}
17:00 - A couple enters. It's Danya and Mikhail Kovalenko, a farmer family who lives nearby.


> (link:"Well good afternoon to you both. How is my favourite family?")[
(set: $family_choices to $family_choices + 1)
(go-to:"KovalenkoFamily")
]
<br>
> (link-goto:"Danya, Mikhail! how is the farm? almost time to start planting I bet.", "KovalenkoFarm")


:: LeaveUkraine {"position":"5350,0","size":"100,100"}
You chose to leave Ukraine and flee the war, like millions of other refugees.


(link-goto: "End.", "Start")


:: Lenny1 {"position":"2050,425","size":"100,100"}
Lenny: Why the face, my friend, aren’t you happy to see your old pal Lenny?

> (link-goto:"Oh it's all this bother on the news, it's enough to get anyone feeling nervous", "Lenny2")
(if: $family_choices >= 2)[
> (link-goto: "Well... Some of my customers are having a hard time, I'm not made of stone. Besides... the news.", "Lenny2")
]


:: Lenny2 {"position":"2050,525","size":"100,100"}
Lenny: Ah yes... the news. Since you are one of my best clients, there's something we should discuss.

> (link-goto:"What is it ?", "Lenny3")


:: Lenny3 {"position":"2050,625","size":"100,100"}
Lenny: Well... I hear there is a war coming, a real one this time. So I'm getting ready.

> (link-goto:"You mean you're gonna run away?", "Lenny4")


:: Lenny4 {"position":"2050,725","size":"100,100"}
Lenny: Haha, not even close, but I am going to make sure me and my own are well protected during this difficult time... that's why I am coming to you with an idea.

> (link-goto:"What do you mean..?", "Lenny5")


:: Lenny5 {"position":"2050,825","size":"100,100"}
Lenny: Alright, listen up. I can offer you a bigger restock this time: 150% instead of the usual. No extra charge today. But here’s the thing. I had to pull some favors to get this much. If you take the extra stock, I need to know you’ll be able to cover my costs down the line. That means you’ll have to **bump up your prices** a little—just enough to keep things steady. Otherwise, I can’t afford to keep doing you favors like this.

> (link:"Well... I’m not sure about this whole war thing, but I can’t let my clients starve. Better to have more than not enough. (Take 150%, increase prices)")[
(set: $stock to 150)
(set: $extra_refill to true)
(go-to: "LennyIncrease")
]
<br>
> (link: "You’re trying to use a crisis to exploit people? That’s not the kind of business I want to run. (Take the regular shipment, keep current prices)")[
(set: $stock to 100)
(set: $extra_refill to false)
(go-to: "LennyCallout")
]


:: LennyCallout {"position":"2000,1025","size":"100,100"}
Lenny: You're a better man than I am, always looking out for those little clients of yours. Well, goodnight and good luck!

(link-goto:"Lenny leaves.", "EndDay1")


:: LennyIncrease {"position":"2125,1025","size":"100,100"}
Lenny: That's the spirit. We need to survive. See you around.

(link-goto:"Lenny leaves.", "EndDay1")


:: LennyStart {"position":"2050,300","size":"100,100"}
19:00 - As you're getting ready to close the shop, a man enters. It's Lenny, your shop's supplier.


(link-goto:"Is it restocking time already?", "Lenny1")


:: Looters1 {"position":"5400,1900","size":"100,100"}
Vlad: Are you sure? Y’know, maybe you were mistaken... I heard on the news that violent looters are roaming the streets.

> (link-goto: "Are you blind or just drunk? You know as well as I do who those men were. Well Vlad, do you feel protected? Is all this what you wanted all along?", "Looters2")


:: Looters2 {"position":"5400,2000","size":"100,100"}
Vlad: Look, politics are one thing... What those brutes did to you is quite another. I promise you, you are my friend, and anyone who comes after my friend is my enemy forever. Besides, hurting an unarmed civilians is unbecoming of any man... I am truly sorry.

> (link-goto: "That’s a lovely sentiment, but my shop is ransacked, completely destroyed. I'm ruined.", "Ruined")


:: Luna1 {"position":"1275,425","size":"100,100"}
Gabi Luna: I am so tired! The little one's been sick all week and I haven't even had time to do laundry or find a new job... I'll just get some milk and flour today
